File image. JOHANNESBURG - Embattled power utility Eskom has announced stage three load shedding. It will run from 1pm on Wednesday until 6am on Thursday. READ: Anger over new load-shedding schedule Eskom says the grid is constrained due to high generation unit breakdowns over the past three days. They're calling on South Africans to use electricity sparingly. #PowerAlert1
Stage 3 loadshedding will be implemented from 13:00 this afternoon until 06:00 in the morning
